      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a classic example of how government regulation directly impacts small business profitability. Increased labor costs force businesses to either raise prices, which can drive away customers, or reduce their operating margins. In smaller towns, where profit margins are already tight, these mandated increases often lead to hiring freezes or reduced hours. Ultimately, businesses need to be able to manage their costs without excessive external pressure.",
