    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's an interesting way to look at it. But if that's the case, why do so many small business owners feel like it's a massive threat to their survival? It feels like there's a huge gap between the economic theory you're describing and what people on the ground are actually experiencing. Is the theory just not applicable to real-world small businesses?",
