      "content": "The gap exists because the theory assumes perfect market conditions that small businesses rarely experience. In reality, small businesses often operate on razor-thin margins where every extra dollar in labor cost is a direct threat to solvency. Furthermore, the theory often ignores the practical limitations of small operations, which cannot absorb large, sudden increases in fixed costs as easily as large corporations.",
